ublisher, advertising, and operations expertise to help us build out our offerings for users, advertisers, and partners; applying her experience building successful digital advertising offerings for internet media giants to our own ads platform; and, through it all, working to grow our business while staying true to the things that make Reddit unique.</p></blockquote>\n<p>Despite claiming 330 million monthly active users, Reddit is still a relatively small operation by Silicon Valley standards. A major part of that is that they&#8217;ve been slow to build out a sophisticated advertising product, though in recent months they&#8217;ve begun rolling out native ads in the company&#8217;s mobile apps.</p>\n<p>“Jen is a seasoned digital veteran and successful executive at some of the biggest media companies in the world, her experience and vision will help carry <span class=\"il\">Reddit</span>’s momentum forward in the years to come,” Reddit CEO Steve Huffman said in a statement.</p>\n<div class=\"feedflare\">\n<a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?a=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:2mJPEYqXBVI\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?d=2mJPEYqXBVI\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?a=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:7Q72WNTAKBA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?d=7Q72WNTAKBA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?a=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:yIl2AUoC8zA\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?d=yIl2AUoC8zA\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?a=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:-BTjWOF_DHI\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?i=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:-BTjWOF_DHI\" border=\"0\"></img></a> <a href=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?a=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:D7DqB2pKExk\"><img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~ff/Techcrunch?i=_4kKJk6AV3E:M5Ovu20PR5o:D7DqB2pKExk\" border=\"0\"></img>